WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.351 --> 00:00:04.372
(ethereal music)

2
00:00:15.436 --> 00:00:17.169
<v Voiceover>There was a bright,</v>

3
00:00:17.169 --> 00:00:19.043
brilliant, white figure

4
00:00:19.043 --> 00:00:22.074
reflected in the windshield of the car.

5
00:00:22.074 --> 00:00:24.078
And I had the assurance that

6
00:00:24.078 --> 00:00:27.028
everything was gonna be alright.

7
00:00:27.028 --> 00:00:29.040
<v Voiceover>He said, I'm going to be with you</v>

8
00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:31.298
for a long time, I've

9
00:00:31.298 --> 00:00:33.508
I've known you for all your life

10
00:00:33.508 --> 00:00:37.621
and I've been your guardian angel all of your life.

11
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:38.824
<v Voiceover>I looked back up</v>

12
00:00:38.824 --> 00:00:40.892
and the face was still there

13
00:00:40.892 --> 00:00:45.697
and it was a warm feeling that the eyes were giving me.

14
00:00:45.697 --> 00:00:50.512
And instead of being frightened, I knew it was okay.

15
00:00:50.512 --> 00:00:51.504
<v Voiceover>The angel</v>

16
00:00:51.504 --> 00:00:54.701
who was present in that room touched me,

17
00:00:54.701 --> 00:00:57.466
and that made all the difference.

18
00:00:57.466 --> 00:00:59.844
<v Voiceover>At that moment, I just felt</v>

19
00:00:59.844 --> 00:01:03.932
peace, and the thoughts quit going through my head

20
00:01:03.932 --> 00:01:07.279
all at once, and it was just

21
00:01:07.279 --> 00:01:10.605
one of the most wonderful feelings I've ever had.

22
00:01:10.605 --> 00:01:13.041
<v Voiceover>Angel's don't want the attention on them</v>

23
00:01:13.041 --> 00:01:17.118
they want us focused beyond them.

24
00:01:22.123 --> 00:01:24.270
<v Voiceover>And it's that angelic presence that binds us</v>

25
00:01:24.270 --> 00:01:26.204
into one anothers' lives

26
00:01:26.204 --> 00:01:27.725
then we become so much more open

27
00:01:27.725 --> 00:01:31.525
to each other.

28
00:01:31.525 --> 00:01:33.461
<v ->Yes I do, I definitely do.</v>

29
00:01:33.461 --> 00:01:35.727
<v ->Well sure, I mean you know, what else?</v>

30
00:01:35.727 --> 00:01:37.138
<v ->Sure I believe in them.</v>

31
00:01:37.138 --> 00:01:38.918
<v ->I gotta believe something's looking out for me.</v>

32
00:01:38.918 --> 00:01:40.204
<v ->Yes, I do.</v>

33
00:01:40.204 --> 00:01:40.895
<v ->Yes.</v>

34
00:01:40.895 --> 00:01:42.183
<v ->Sure I believe in 'em.</v>

35
00:01:42.183 --> 00:01:43.234
<v ->No, I don't.</v>

36
00:01:43.234 --> 00:01:44.389
<v ->If it had not been for angels,</v>

37
00:01:44.389 --> 00:01:46.177
I wouldn't even be alive today.

38
00:01:46.177 --> 00:01:48.460
<v ->During the time my father was ill,</v>

39
00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:52.543
in the hospital... she appeared to me

40
00:01:52.543 --> 00:01:55.757
and stayed with me the entire time he was ill

41
00:01:55.757 --> 00:01:58.803
and the day he died, she disappeared.

42
00:01:58.803 --> 00:02:01.665
<v ->There's been too many times in my past,</v>

43
00:02:01.665 --> 00:02:05.416
or possibly in your own past where,

44
00:02:05.416 --> 00:02:07.786
very frankly, you've made it out of some scrapes

45
00:02:07.786 --> 00:02:09.284
somebody had to been watching over you.

46
00:02:09.284 --> 00:02:11.149
<v ->I been at crossroads in my life,</v>

47
00:02:11.149 --> 00:02:15.617
or in danger and they've just been there

48
00:02:15.617 --> 00:02:16.554
to protect me

49
00:02:16.554 --> 00:02:18.393
<v ->They're sort of like messengers</v>

50
00:02:18.393 --> 00:02:20.121
and they may even carry secrets of

51
00:02:20.121 --> 00:02:21.743
the most inner part of the heart.

52
00:02:21.743 --> 00:02:23.768
<v ->It's a little bit like believing in ghosts I guess.</v>

53
00:02:23.768 --> 00:02:27.896
I just, never seen one, never met one.

54
00:02:27.896 --> 00:02:31.169
So I have no other way to believe in 'em.

55
00:02:31.169 --> 00:02:33.407
<v ->For an example, my dad</v>

56
00:02:33.407 --> 00:02:36.507
when I was 11 years old he was in an accident.

57
00:02:36.507 --> 00:02:39.081
He had an extensive brain injury.

58
00:02:39.081 --> 00:02:40.992
He stayed unconscious for a little over a year

59
00:02:40.992 --> 00:02:43.715
in Phoenix, Arizona in the hospital.

60
00:02:43.715 --> 00:02:46.584
But he says when he woke up, there was an angel

61
00:02:46.584 --> 00:02:49.771
that was at the foot of his bed and the thing

62
00:02:49.771 --> 00:02:52.216
about it is when he woke up

63
00:02:52.216 --> 00:02:53.144
he had been laying there

64
00:02:53.144 --> 00:02:54.559
and they had been rolling him in sheets

65
00:02:54.559 --> 00:02:56.995
to keep down bed sores and what have you

66
00:02:56.995 --> 00:03:01.356
and he had lost weight, he was just a skeleton you might say

67
00:03:01.356 --> 00:03:03.468
and that day he got up out of that bed

68
00:03:03.468 --> 00:03:06.924
and walked to the bathroom by hisself.

69
00:03:06.924 --> 00:03:09.211
<v Voiceover>My name is Pam Kidd.</v>

70
00:03:09.211 --> 00:03:11.589
While doing research for my magazine assignment

71
00:03:11.589 --> 00:03:13.350
on the subject of angels,

72
00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:16.988
I came to one undeniable conclusion

73
00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:21.151
angel believers are all around.

74
00:03:21.151 --> 00:03:24.316
In fact a recent Time Magazine article

75
00:03:24.316 --> 00:03:27.368
announced that 69% of Americans believe

76
00:03:27.368 --> 00:03:29.728
that angels exist.

77
00:03:29.728 --> 00:03:32.944
And 46% of the population are convinced

78
00:03:32.944 --> 00:03:36.283
that they have their own guardian angel.

79
00:03:36.283 --> 00:03:39.844
Well actually, if you take a look at the big picture

80
00:03:39.844 --> 00:03:41.870
angels have been a part of people's lives

81
00:03:41.870 --> 00:03:45.256
in every age across the planet.

82
00:03:45.256 --> 00:03:47.903
And respected authorities like John Ronner

83
00:03:47.903 --> 00:03:50.581
author of two best selling angel books

84
00:03:50.581 --> 00:03:53.746
have discovered something through extensive research.

85
00:03:53.746 --> 00:03:57.288
<v ->In 1990 it was a Gallup poll showing that</v>

86
00:03:57.288 --> 00:04:00.582
13% of respondents felt that they had encountered

87
00:04:00.582 --> 00:04:03.095
an angel or some other supernatural being

88
00:04:03.095 --> 00:04:04.222
and that's a lot of people there

89
00:04:04.222 --> 00:04:05.727
that's over 30 million people if you

90
00:04:05.727 --> 00:04:07.882
extrapolate that out to the population

91
00:04:07.882 --> 00:04:09.376
six times the population

92
00:04:09.376 --> 00:04:11.986
of my home state of Tennessee.

93
00:04:11.986 --> 00:04:13.217
And many polls just like this

94
00:04:13.217 --> 00:04:15.506
the thing that is intriguing about this is

95
00:04:15.506 --> 00:04:18.436
the polls are unanimous

96
00:04:18.436 --> 00:04:20.778
they don't deviate one from the other

97
00:04:20.778 --> 00:04:23.118
they all indicate that a substantial minority of us

98
00:04:23.118 --> 00:04:25.043
are having these experiences.

99
00:04:25.043 --> 00:04:28.839
<v ->And if we go back just 150 years in our culture,</v>

100
00:04:28.839 --> 00:04:31.786
it was perfectly okay to talk about these things.

101
00:04:31.786 --> 00:04:35.440
Our great-grandparents knew about this kind of thing

102
00:04:35.440 --> 00:04:37.892
very well and would talk about this

103
00:04:37.892 --> 00:04:42.680
and families would discuss visitations with the deceased

104
00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:45.810
and what happened to Grandpa on his deathbed

105
00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:48.419
and how he said that he saw a light

106
00:04:48.419 --> 00:04:51.196
and saw Grandma coming to him

107
00:04:51.196 --> 00:04:54.295
in those last few moments and so on.

108
00:04:54.295 --> 00:04:56.380
Then we went through a period I suppose

109
00:04:56.380 --> 00:04:59.777
into this century where it just became

110
00:04:59.777 --> 00:05:02.387
not so respectable to talk about these things

111
00:05:02.387 --> 00:05:04.919
and they were dismissed and people thought

112
00:05:04.919 --> 00:05:09.337
that these were old wives' tales and superstitions.

113
00:05:09.337 --> 00:05:12.263
<v ->I think what's happening rather than it being a fad</v>

114
00:05:12.263 --> 00:05:14.199
is that we are reconnecting with a

115
00:05:14.199 --> 00:05:16.053
critical part of ourselves that we have been

116
00:05:16.053 --> 00:05:18.966
cut off from in western civilization.

117
00:05:18.966 --> 00:05:21.339
<v ->We interpret it to be a discovery</v>

118
00:05:21.339 --> 00:05:23.989
well it's really not, it's a rediscovery.

119
00:05:23.989 --> 00:05:25.723
These things are part and parcel

120
00:05:25.723 --> 00:05:27.628
of being a human being.

121
00:05:27.628 --> 00:05:30.868
And people have had spiritual experiences

122
00:05:30.868 --> 00:05:34.649
as long as there have been people.

123
00:05:34.649 --> 00:05:36.918
<v Voiceover>Like most issues of faith,</v>

124
00:05:36.918 --> 00:05:39.187
believing that a supreme being has devised

125
00:05:39.187 --> 00:05:41.863
this marvelous scheme that shadows

126
00:05:41.863 --> 00:05:44.232
each of us with a caring sponsor

127
00:05:44.232 --> 00:05:46.627
patron, messenger, guide,

128
00:05:46.627 --> 00:05:49.330
whatever you might call your angel

129
00:05:49.330 --> 00:05:53.670
it's something you have to simply believe.

130
00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:55.570
A short run through history can't help

131
00:05:55.570 --> 00:05:59.009
but reinforce and refresh the angel believers confidence

132
00:05:59.009 --> 00:06:00.845
on the subject.

133
00:06:00.845 --> 00:06:02.714
From the beginning,

134
00:06:02.714 --> 00:06:05.283
artist's brush and sculptor's chisel

135
00:06:05.283 --> 00:06:09.573
were expressing this age old angel notion.

136
00:06:09.573 --> 00:06:12.690
If you doubt their prevalence look around

137
00:06:12.690 --> 00:06:15.559
try conducting your own angel search.

138
00:06:15.559 --> 00:06:17.461
When my husband and I had a chance to visit

139
00:06:17.461 --> 00:06:19.941
several countries a few years ago

140
00:06:19.941 --> 00:06:23.731
I used my camera for a private angel hunt.

141
00:06:23.731 --> 00:06:25.731
I found them on fountains,

142
00:06:25.731 --> 00:06:30.345
atop street signs, on the facades of public buildings

143
00:06:30.345 --> 00:06:32.677
on the door posts of private homes

144
00:06:32.677 --> 00:06:35.319
angels everywhere.

145
00:06:35.319 --> 00:06:38.849
Remarkable, the lengths we go to depict angels

146
00:06:38.849 --> 00:06:40.778
when so few of us have seen angels

147
00:06:40.778 --> 00:06:42.791
face to face.

148
00:06:42.791 --> 00:06:47.254
Or is it really that rare?

149
00:06:47.254 --> 00:06:49.557
Alive today, who have actually

150
00:06:49.557 --> 00:06:52.930
looked into the eye of an angel?

151
00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:54.786
Steve Hooper suffering from

152
00:06:54.786 --> 00:06:57.603
a severe and painful blood disorder

153
00:06:57.603 --> 00:07:00.540
awoke one night to an unexpected visitor

154
00:07:00.540 --> 00:07:03.174
<v ->The room was just filled with a light</v>

155
00:07:03.174 --> 00:07:05.029
the brightest, whitest light

156
00:07:05.029 --> 00:07:07.264
I've ever seen in my life.

157
00:07:07.264 --> 00:07:09.234
And at the foot of the bed

158
00:07:09.234 --> 00:07:14.018
was a figure... it was a man

159
00:07:14.018 --> 00:07:16.554
had shoulder length hair

160
00:07:16.554 --> 00:07:17.355
I could not make out

161
00:07:17.355 --> 00:07:20.404
any other features of the face.

162
00:07:20.404 --> 00:07:25.300
But the warmth filled the room

163
00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:28.346
the love filled the room it filled my body

164
00:07:28.346 --> 00:07:31.479
I could just feel it all through me

165
00:07:31.479 --> 00:07:33.677
working all through me.

166
00:07:33.677 --> 00:07:35.206
I could actually see the wings,

167
00:07:35.206 --> 00:07:38.115
they were folded against the back

168
00:07:38.115 --> 00:07:39.934
and stood about a foot

169
00:07:39.934 --> 00:07:43.734
above the top of his head

170
00:07:43.734 --> 00:07:45.990
The only thing he spoke to me was

171
00:07:45.990 --> 00:07:48.513
I am the angel of mercy.

172
00:07:48.513 --> 00:07:50.807
The next morning I asked my wife

173
00:07:50.807 --> 00:07:52.873
did you see her or hear anything strange

174
00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:53.925
in the middle of the night?

175
00:07:53.925 --> 00:07:56.767
And she says no, did the dog wake you again?

176
00:07:56.767 --> 00:07:58.296
And I said, no.

177
00:07:58.296 --> 00:08:00.554
She seemed to be okay, but did you

178
00:08:00.554 --> 00:08:03.827
see or feel or hear anything besides that?

179
00:08:03.827 --> 00:08:07.191
She said she hadn't.

180
00:08:07.191 --> 00:08:09.810
I said don't worry about my iron test

181
00:08:09.810 --> 00:08:10.945
coming up next month,

182
00:08:10.945 --> 00:08:13.164
I know it's gonna be okay.

183
00:08:13.164 --> 00:08:16.067
I've had the reassurance that everything is fine.

184
00:08:16.067 --> 00:08:17.908
<v Voiceover>And it was.</v>

185
00:08:17.908 --> 00:08:21.252
Steve's next blood test came back normal.

186
00:08:21.252 --> 00:08:25.568
Which according to his doctor was a near miracle.

187
00:08:27.858 --> 00:08:30.595
<v Voiceover>Office Randy Salazar found himself</v>

188
00:08:30.595 --> 00:08:33.264
in a terrible moral dilemma.

189
00:08:33.264 --> 00:08:35.930
A situation where the lives of an entire room

190
00:08:35.930 --> 00:08:39.173
full of innocent people depended on what he did next.

191
00:08:39.173 --> 00:08:42.276
<v ->The doctor said, take the handcuffs off the prisoner.</v>

192
00:08:42.276 --> 00:08:44.605
And I told the doctor, I said, he's...

193
00:08:44.605 --> 00:08:45.743
I've had problems with this guy

194
00:08:45.743 --> 00:08:47.261
he's very combative, I don't want to.

195
00:08:47.261 --> 00:08:50.198
He says, I'm the doctor you take the handcuffs off.

196
00:08:50.198 --> 00:08:53.187
I said okay, so I took the handcuffs off this man.

197
00:08:53.187 --> 00:08:54.808
The doctor was examining him

198
00:08:54.808 --> 00:08:58.228
and then he went through a series of questions

199
00:08:58.228 --> 00:09:00.848
to see how coherent he was.

200
00:09:00.848 --> 00:09:03.204
One of the questions was,

201
00:09:03.204 --> 00:09:04.699
What is today?

202
00:09:04.699 --> 00:09:08.645
And the prisoner said, today is Monday.

203
00:09:08.645 --> 00:09:11.144
And right then I looked in the prisoner's eyes

204
00:09:11.144 --> 00:09:13.937
and I said, and today is the day I kill you.

205
00:09:13.937 --> 00:09:15.737
But I said it in my mind, I didn't say it

206
00:09:15.737 --> 00:09:17.178
where you could hear it.

207
00:09:17.178 --> 00:09:19.544
And I'm wondering, why did I say that?

208
00:09:19.544 --> 00:09:23.318
Then, later on my partner arrived

209
00:09:23.318 --> 00:09:25.833
and we're there on the prisoner

210
00:09:25.833 --> 00:09:27.519
and he's being very combative.

211
00:09:27.519 --> 00:09:31.622
And then my partner and I heard a tray of dishes

212
00:09:31.622 --> 00:09:33.611
or something fall down the hallway.

213
00:09:33.611 --> 00:09:37.745
And we turned our faces to look to see what it was

214
00:09:37.745 --> 00:09:40.714
and at that point the prisoner jumped off the gurney

215
00:09:40.714 --> 00:09:43.067
and grabbed my partner around the waist.

216
00:09:43.067 --> 00:09:45.358
And at first I didn't think he saw his

217
00:09:45.358 --> 00:09:47.535
gun that he had stuck in his belt

218
00:09:47.535 --> 00:09:50.721
but he felt the gun and he pulled the gun out.

219
00:09:50.721 --> 00:09:53.107
I had no alternative but to pull my weapon

220
00:09:53.107 --> 00:09:56.083
and I, as soon as my partner

221
00:09:56.083 --> 00:09:58.682
and the prisoner fell to the floor

222
00:09:58.682 --> 00:10:01.082
I saw the gun pointed straight towards my

223
00:10:01.082 --> 00:10:04.088
partner's chest and I told Bob Russell, I said,

224
00:10:04.088 --> 00:10:05.757
Bob, get out of the way

225
00:10:05.757 --> 00:10:09.570
and I fired one shot into the abdomen of the prisoner

226
00:10:09.570 --> 00:10:13.738
he fell back, with the gun in his hand

227
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:17.313
and, much to my amazement he sat back up

228
00:10:17.313 --> 00:10:19.557
still and he pointed the gun at me.

229
00:10:19.557 --> 00:10:21.959
I stepped one step over to get out of the way

230
00:10:21.959 --> 00:10:24.525
But there, remember there's other people in this room

231
00:10:24.525 --> 00:10:26.137
and I'm thinking if he gets a shot off

232
00:10:26.137 --> 00:10:27.671
he's gonna kill somebody.

233
00:10:27.671 --> 00:10:29.696
At that point, I stood back

234
00:10:29.696 --> 00:10:32.823
and cocked the hammer back on my weapon

235
00:10:32.823 --> 00:10:36.976
and this image appeared on the wall

236
00:10:36.976 --> 00:10:41.065
and stated in a clear voice

237
00:10:41.065 --> 00:10:43.411
aimed at center that way you'll hit something

238
00:10:43.411 --> 00:10:46.397
if you miss a little bit so I

239
00:10:46.397 --> 00:10:48.566
I pointed my gun and I shot the man

240
00:10:48.566 --> 00:10:51.301
right through the, shot him through the heart.

241
00:10:51.301 --> 00:10:52.789
<v Voiceover>After the shooting</v>

242
00:10:52.789 --> 00:10:55.807
Salazar was naturally in agony over what had happened.

243
00:10:55.807 --> 00:10:57.471
He went to his mother's and his father's house

244
00:10:57.471 --> 00:10:59.414
to try to get some sort of comfort.

245
00:10:59.414 --> 00:11:01.416
<v ->And I stepped out and I took a few steps</v>

246
00:11:01.416 --> 00:11:05.178
towards their walkway that led up to the front door.

247
00:11:05.178 --> 00:11:07.986
I noticed something out of the corner of my eye.

248
00:11:07.986 --> 00:11:10.851
And at first I thought it was a light

249
00:11:10.851 --> 00:11:14.738
like a fluorescent light which was above the fence.

250
00:11:14.738 --> 00:11:17.708
And above this fence that was, that's

251
00:11:17.708 --> 00:11:21.106
seven to eight feet high, there was a face

252
00:11:21.106 --> 00:11:24.095
And there was this face that was looking at me

253
00:11:24.095 --> 00:11:27.001
very distinct, the eyes, nose, mouth and everything

254
00:11:27.001 --> 00:11:28.736
very pleasant and it was just looking at me

255
00:11:28.736 --> 00:11:31.215
and as I walked slowly towards the door

256
00:11:31.215 --> 00:11:34.642
the eyes of this face followed me.

257
00:11:34.642 --> 00:11:39.113
And I blinked and I stopped two-thirds of the way up

258
00:11:39.113 --> 00:11:42.119
to see if I was just you know, thinking this in my mind

259
00:11:42.119 --> 00:11:43.647
And it could not have been a person

260
00:11:43.647 --> 00:11:45.616
standing behind that fence because

261
00:11:45.616 --> 00:11:48.836
the face itself from the chin to the top of the head

