00:31:01.243 --> 00:31:04.110
"He who dies with the most toys wins."

647
00:31:04.110 --> 00:31:05.815
We're not to be like the Pharaohs,

648
00:31:05.815 --> 00:31:07.303
you know, amassing treasures

649
00:31:07.303 --> 00:31:09.131
and then baring it all with ourselves,

650
00:31:09.131 --> 00:31:10.753
there's something more to this life.

651
00:31:10.753 --> 00:31:12.654
<v ->This one philosopher said,</v>

652
00:31:12.654 --> 00:31:15.652
there's a God-shaped hole in each of us

653
00:31:15.652 --> 00:31:18.494
and it can only be filled with God.

654
00:31:18.494 --> 00:31:20.830
And what happens is, I think.

655
00:31:20.830 --> 00:31:23.734
We try to fill it with a lot of other things,

656
00:31:23.734 --> 00:31:26.643
we've had decades you know

657
00:31:26.643 --> 00:31:30.422
maybe from the early 60s when we took God out of everything

658
00:31:30.422 --> 00:31:32.107
we didn't need Him in our schools anymore,

659
00:31:32.107 --> 00:31:34.044
we weren't going to pray to Him in public,

660
00:31:34.044 --> 00:31:36.246
God was reserved for Sunday mornings,

661
00:31:36.246 --> 00:31:39.068
if you wanted to even make the effort.

662
00:31:39.068 --> 00:31:41.077
And we were a stalwart people,

663
00:31:41.077 --> 00:31:43.019
we were a proud people

664
00:31:43.019 --> 00:31:45.802
we didn't need to be on our knees.

665
00:31:45.802 --> 00:31:49.358
And that evolved into a culture of drugs,

666
00:31:49.358 --> 00:31:51.394
that was where we were going to find our God

